  "title": "Cognitive Viability",
  "question": "Is my cognitive system — capacity, focus, and growth — still intact?",
  "whatsUnderThreat": "The full cognitive system that produced — and continues to extend — the judgment AI now amplifies. Three risks running in parallel: core-capacity atrophy as I delegate the work; erosion of executive function (focus, working memory across concurrent threads); and quiet cessation of the conceptual and lexical accretion that has always renewed the craft.",
  "headlineMeasurementId": "self-generated-reasoning-ratio",
  "fieldLink": "research.html#cognitive",
  "reading": {
    "asOf": "2026-Q2",
    "text": "Maintenance signals holding inside expected band; growth signals show practitioner-introduced novelty trailing agent-introduced novelty roughly 1:3, consistent with early AI-native practice. Concurrency self-report tracks below activity-side count — the gap is the live signal to watch."
  },
